WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.480 --> 00:00:03.159
Hey, good morning family, praise the Lord.

00:00:03.159 --> 00:00:04.945
Thank you for joining us again today.

00:00:05.200 --> 00:00:06.799
We're excited to be here.

00:00:08.342 --> 00:00:09.508
Well, praise the Lord.

00:00:09.508 --> 00:00:28.731
Yes, we're here to work it; we have work to do, a path to clear, a road to lay.

00:00:28.731 --> 00:00:41.760
Everything is so important in the spirit realm right now.

00:00:41.760 --> 00:00:53.495
I have such an urgency; Diana and I both do.

00:00:53.495 --> 00:01:07.263
I want you to visualize what he was saying yesterday: acting like it's already done.

00:01:07.263 --> 00:01:29.845
For your miracle, what would you do if you got what you're believing for in the next five minutes?

00:01:29.845 --> 00:02:01.386
If you knew the breakthrough was coming through in the next five minutes and you could set your timer on it, what would you do?

00:02:01.386 --> 00:02:06.213
How would you act?

00:02:06.213 --> 00:02:23.400
In just that split second he downloaded that to me yesterday, he said, 'Act like you've already got it.

00:02:23.400 --> 00:02:37.382
' Let your praise, like Brother Hagin said, let your praises equal your prayers.

00:02:37.382 --> 00:02:54.623
If you're praying a lot about it, let it be like a scale in the spirit realm.

00:03:05.973 --> 00:03:13.760
Let your praises elevate and go up as much as you're praying about it.

00:03:13.760 --> 00:03:17.260
Praise, prayer; praise, prayer.

00:03:17.260 --> 00:03:37.311
So that you're glorifying God and you're praying, but you're taking the care out of your prayer.

00:03:37.311 --> 00:03:48.000
We're not begging believers; we're believing believers that realize the manifestation is coming.

00:03:48.000 --> 00:04:04.902
We're not trying to persuade God to give us something: 'God, please, please bring my miracle.

00:04:04.902 --> 00:04:08.000
' No, thank you.

00:04:22.004 --> 00:04:22.235
I'm taking the care and the worry.

00:04:22.235 --> 00:04:32.217
'Oh God, they gave me a bad report.

00:04:32.217 --> 00:04:52.873
Oh God, they told me that they're going to come and repo our car tomorrow, or I don't have enough money tomorrow.

00:04:52.873 --> 00:05:06.782
Lord, the light bill is due and I need a new pair of shoes.

00:05:06.782 --> 00:05:25.862
' You've got all this care because of the deadline, the pressure of time.

00:05:25.862 --> 00:05:30.879
Bending to the pressure of time—the pressure is always on you.

00:05:31.279 --> 00:05:54.680
The bills are always due, the kids need food, the kids need new shoes, new clothes, the school is wanting some kind of field trip.

00:05:54.680 --> 00:06:08.084
You've got a need, but the care of the world weighs on our shoulders.

00:06:08.084 --> 00:06:10.863
It's just human nature.

00:06:10.863 --> 00:06:41.630
But read that scripture: 'Be careful for nothing, but in everything by prayer and supplication with thanksgiving, let your requests be made known unto God.

00:06:41.630 --> 00:06:48.199
' So with thanksgiving, yes.

00:06:48.199 --> 00:06:59.546
That's what he was telling me: act like you've already got it.

00:06:59.546 --> 00:07:21.039
Get into the prayer vein of believing that you've received it before you've got it, and stay in the atmosphere of saying, 'Thank you, Father.

00:07:21.039 --> 00:07:32.039
I just believe I'm going to receive.

00:07:32.039 --> 00:07:49.915
' I'm not going to take the care of 'I've got to have this right now.

00:07:49.915 --> 00:08:40.680
' I thought this was interesting also in 1 Peter 3:7: 'Husbands, likewise, dwell with them with understanding, giving honor to the wife as to the weaker vessel and as being heirs together of the grace of life, that your prayers may not be hindered.

00:08:40.680 --> 00:09:02.170
' So he's saying if you're not honoring your wife and you're not treating her right, your prayers will be hindered.

00:09:02.170 --> 00:09:29.035
1 Peter 3:7 states that if we don't honor our wives and treat them right, your prayers aren't going to be heard; they're going to be hindered.

00:09:29.035 --> 00:09:37.006
There is a flow of honoring your spouse.

00:09:37.006 --> 00:09:56.870
Wife, honor your husband too, but there is a flow as the head of the house.

00:09:56.870 --> 00:10:22.491
If you are treating your wife like trash and you're just a bully, your prayers will be hindered.

00:10:31.360 --> 00:10:40.896
Those scriptures pop out and make you realize it's all an equilibrium.

00:10:40.896 --> 00:11:08.398
The spirit realm is alive, and to get things active like an engine, you've got all the pistons firing, the fan belt, all of it going.

00:11:08.398 --> 00:11:20.863
But if one thing is off, that car won't go very far.

00:11:20.863 --> 00:11:47.029
When you put your prayer and you get all the things in motion like that engine, that car has the ability to go really fast.

00:11:47.029 --> 00:11:59.800
But if it's off just even by a little bit, the whole thing is off-kilter.

00:11:59.800 --> 00:12:10.839
If you get the timing belt wrong, you're going to throw a rod; it's over.

00:12:21.386 --> 00:12:23.532
I'm trying to compare prayer and walking by faith to an engine.

00:12:23.532 --> 00:12:47.919
How do you make the engine in the spirit realm run at 100 miles per hour so that we're doing it full force and not having these delayed responses?

00:12:47.919 --> 00:12:51.030
Faith works by love.

00:12:51.030 --> 00:13:00.475
If you're not walking in love, you're not going to get your blessing.

00:13:00.475 --> 00:13:08.873
Love takes no account of a suffered wrong.

00:13:08.873 --> 00:13:28.519
When people talk bad about you on the internet, I take no account of suffering wrong.

00:13:28.519 --> 00:14:02.370
There are plenty of times I could do it every day, and I go, 'Oh God, help me, Father, to take no account of a suffered wrong.

00:14:02.370 --> 00:14:20.542
' These people are running me down on Twitter, on X, and saying all sorts of things.

00:14:20.542 --> 00:14:27.269
Love takes no account of a suffered wrong.

00:14:27.269 --> 00:14:49.576
Help me to come up higher in my love walk because the Bible says that faith works by love.

00:14:49.576 --> 00:15:06.870
God is love, and perfect love casteth out all fear because fear has torment, and fear tolerated is faith contaminated.

00:15:06.870 --> 00:15:15.279
All these things are an equilibrium.

00:15:15.279 --> 00:15:28.594
Getting it in motion so that the prayer engine works.

00:15:28.594 --> 00:15:38.903
How do we make this prayer engine work?

00:15:38.903 --> 00:16:00.685
More praise, more thanksgiving, more glory to God, more honoring him, lifting up holy hands, and keeping your heart right.

00:16:13.031 --> 00:16:23.582
I want impartation from the Holy Spirit every day, and I want to be changed from glory to glory every day.

00:16:23.582 --> 00:16:43.315
I don't want to keep going down the highway the wrong way and wasting time day after day.

00:16:43.315 --> 00:16:49.356
If nothing is changing, it's because it's off-kilter.

00:16:49.356 --> 00:16:55.853
You're going, 'Lord, what's broken in this engine?

00:16:55.853 --> 00:17:24.108
' If I can help you with one thing through these videos and you grab one little thing that changes your life forever, then we've done our job.

00:17:24.456 --> 00:17:32.731
I want to help you get higher in your prayer.

00:17:32.731 --> 00:17:45.924
When the care of life tries to choke you out, that's one of the big ones.

00:17:50.360 --> 00:17:59.867
I try so hard not to pray the care because begging is not believing.

00:17:59.867 --> 00:18:06.815
Get your care out of your prayer.

00:18:21.119 --> 00:18:21.599
Yes, get your care out of your prayer.

00:18:21.599 --> 00:18:33.893
God is not moved by your need; he's moved by your faith.

00:18:33.893 --> 00:18:41.907
Without faith, it is impossible to please him.

00:18:41.907 --> 00:19:05.542
For he that cometh to God must believe that he is and that he is a rewarder of those that diligently seek him.

00:19:06.945 --> 00:19:19.124
I pray that you all get a little something and add that to your engine.

00:19:19.124 --> 00:19:35.040
Instead of going down the same road expecting different results and going, 'Why is my life so messed up?

00:19:35.040 --> 00:20:04.071
' You learn by trial and error, and by listening to Brother Hagin, you go through life's emotions and say, 'Holy Spirit, I can't do this without you.

00:20:04.071 --> 00:20:08.743
' He corrects those he loves.

00:20:14.849 --> 00:20:20.540
I told Diana, 'Do I get a lot right?

00:20:20.540 --> 00:20:32.110
' because I feel I'm always being molded and corrected.

00:20:39.147 --> 00:20:45.587
I want to just be on the right road doing the right thing.

00:20:45.587 --> 00:20:56.173
You can't put a square tire on a car and expect it to run, Brandon.

00:20:56.173 --> 00:21:05.300
You've got to put a round tire on there.

00:21:05.300 --> 00:21:15.173
I walk away, and it happens a lot.

00:21:15.173 --> 00:21:42.859
Even to Brandon, I'll give him a tidbit so he doesn't struggle with this when he gets older.

00:21:42.859 --> 00:21:59.444
Learn it now, Brandon, so when you get to my age, you're far more advanced.

00:22:07.759 --> 00:22:10.789
I don't want my kids to go through those stupid mistakes.

00:22:15.475 --> 00:22:27.160
I was talking about how we bring prayer to a different level—it's bringing a different atmosphere of thanksgiving.

00:22:27.160 --> 00:22:37.054
'God, thank you for what you're about to do.

00:22:37.054 --> 00:22:50.243
' May is almost here; I'm going to anticipate something huge in May.

00:22:50.243 --> 00:22:54.550
Just have that attitude of expectation.

00:22:54.550 --> 00:23:08.314
I am expecting God to show up and show off in my life today.

00:23:08.314 --> 00:23:24.500
Even if you didn't get your breakthrough today, I'm expecting God to show up tomorrow.

00:23:24.500 --> 00:23:31.413
When I open my eyes, I have another opportunity.

00:23:31.413 --> 00:23:41.875
God, I thank you that this is just the beginning.

00:23:44.390 --> 00:23:51.537
I expect God to talk to me whenever I'm praying.

00:23:52.760 --> 00:23:59.577
I said something; he's going to say something.

00:23:59.577 --> 00:24:09.969
He wants to lead and guide me.

00:24:09.969 --> 00:24:28.031
There are some things he tells us that I keep private, for direction for us.

00:24:28.031 --> 00:24:38.619
But I believe God's going to say something as you pray.

00:24:45.607 --> 00:24:49.832
The Bible says, 'I hear my father's voice, and a stranger's voice I won't follow.

00:24:49.832 --> 00:24:57.240
' As you communicate with the Father, you expect expectation back.

00:24:57.240 --> 00:25:09.265
It would be rude if you talked to somebody and they never said anything.

00:25:09.265 --> 00:25:14.969
We keep our spiritual ears open.

00:25:14.969 --> 00:25:17.339
That's exactly where the Lord is.

00:25:17.339 --> 00:25:20.430
He's going to talk.

00:25:20.430 --> 00:25:28.066
It's like a marriage, a dance.

00:25:32.973 --> 00:25:33.239
You lead, I follow.

00:25:33.239 --> 00:25:36.710
He's going to talk.

00:25:36.710 --> 00:25:43.570
Spirit-led prayers—we're being filled on a daily basis.

00:25:43.570 --> 00:25:53.250
It is a dialogue, a two-way conversation.

00:25:59.080 --> 00:26:01.686
My Father loves me, and he talks to me.

00:26:01.686 --> 00:26:06.044
Stop saying, 'I don't hear God.

00:26:06.044 --> 00:26:16.570
' I see it in the comment section all the time.

00:26:16.570 --> 00:26:29.218
Faith calls those things that be not as though they were.

00:26:29.218 --> 00:26:41.404
Start saying, 'I hear my Father talk to me.

00:26:41.404 --> 00:26:48.129
' You have what you say.

00:26:48.129 --> 00:26:57.170
Life and death are in the power of your tongue.

00:26:57.170 --> 00:27:06.297
You are reaping the fruit of everything you're saying.

00:27:06.297 --> 00:27:36.919
If you say, 'God doesn't speak to me,' he's not speaking to you because you don't have ears to hear.

00:27:36.919 --> 00:27:50.372
He that has ears to hear, let him hear what the Spirit is saying.

00:27:50.372 --> 00:27:55.214
I have ears to hear.

00:27:55.214 --> 00:28:04.701
I hear you, Father, even a pin dropping.

00:28:04.701 --> 00:28:17.714
I hear the still, small voice inside of me.

00:28:17.714 --> 00:28:24.474
I hear my Father talk to me.

00:28:24.474 --> 00:28:37.697
I will listen to him, and he will talk to me on a regular basis.

00:28:37.697 --> 00:28:51.399
I will not hear a familiar spirit or a demonic voice.

00:29:13.382 --> 00:29:13.713
I only hear my Father's voice.

00:29:17.155 --> 00:29:21.164
I'm not going to hear you, devil.

00:29:30.760 --> 00:29:32.120
I will not hear audible voices of devils talking to me.

00:29:34.169 --> 00:29:39.408
I only hear what God has to say.

00:29:39.408 --> 00:29:48.596
Start saying that over yourself.

00:29:48.596 --> 00:30:06.976
We always know when it's the devil because it brings confusion, fear, and torment.

00:30:06.976 --> 00:30:13.140
If you're tormented, it isn't God.

00:30:13.140 --> 00:30:19.880
God brings peace and joy.

00:30:19.880 --> 00:30:29.370
'The Ultimate Voice' is a wonderful book by Oral Roberts.

00:30:29.370 --> 00:30:44.991
Just like he says at the end of every chapter, 'So listen, listen again, listen today.

00:30:44.991 --> 00:30:56.291
' He's always speaking, and he doesn't speak just to hear himself talk.

00:30:56.786 --> 00:31:06.799
He speaks to make real things happen in a real world.

00:31:06.799 --> 00:31:11.684
It's called 'The Ultimate Voice' by Oral Roberts.

00:31:13.000 --> 00:31:14.120
Get it, amazing book.

00:31:14.120 --> 00:31:23.592
Keep saying, 'I hear my Father talk to me.

00:31:23.592 --> 00:31:33.360
' I am going to be victorious in every area of my life and I'm going to go after that giant's head and take it.

00:31:33.360 --> 00:31:40.000
Perfect love casteth out all fear.

00:31:40.000 --> 00:31:47.480
If you're hearing fear and tolerating it, it's not God.

00:31:47.480 --> 00:31:55.708
Make sure it's not a spirit of forebodings.

00:31:55.708 --> 00:32:02.639
Come against the spirit of forebodings.

00:32:05.549 --> 00:32:25.817
A spirit of forebodings will always whisper, 'Something bad is about to happen.

00:32:25.817 --> 00:32:52.080
' The Holy Spirit will warn us about things to come, but if you have that caution inside and you have peace, that's him.

00:32:52.080 --> 00:33:09.908
If you don't have peace, the peace is your umpire.

00:33:09.908 --> 00:33:13.039
Follow the peace.

00:33:14.960 --> 00:33:28.459
I have a dear sister who said she didn't have peace about doing something.

00:33:28.459 --> 00:33:32.779
Don't buck peace.

00:33:32.779 --> 00:33:43.399
If you don't have joy and peace, check yourself.

00:33:43.399 --> 00:33:55.348
Never make decisions when you don't have peace.

00:33:55.348 --> 00:34:12.360
If they need an answer right now, the answer is no.

00:34:12.360 --> 00:34:17.960
'No' is a complete sentence.

00:34:17.960 --> 00:34:23.251
I'm following the peace of God.

00:34:23.251 --> 00:34:41.359
When you follow the peace of God, peace follows on your marriage, your children, and your finances.

00:34:41.359 --> 00:34:50.289
Father, we just lift up this body right now.

00:34:50.289 --> 00:35:12.747
I thank you, Father, that you were wounded for our transgressions and bruised for our iniquities.

00:35:12.747 --> 00:35:30.409
The chastisement of our peace was upon you, and with your stripes, we are healed.

00:35:30.409 --> 00:35:39.600
Thank you for what you did for us 2,000 years ago.

00:35:39.600 --> 00:35:53.865
Jesus, you are the ultimate sacrifice, the Lamb slain before the foundation of the world.

00:35:53.865 --> 00:36:15.480
We're grateful for all you've provided: for the air in our lungs, the food, the drink, the clothes on our backs.

00:36:32.567 --> 00:36:32.902
We lift up the blood before you.

00:36:33.236 --> 00:36:59.834
We can confess our sins to you privately, and you are faithful and just to forgive us and cleanse us from all unrighteousness.

00:36:59.834 --> 00:37:16.760
Holy Spirit, take me from glory to glory and correct me.

00:37:20.133 --> 00:37:23.520
You are the captain of my ship.

00:37:24.909 --> 00:37:32.204
Thank you, Lord, that you've never given up on us.

00:37:35.260 --> 00:37:43.319
You sent angels; we have bodyguards in the heavenlies protecting us right now.

00:37:52.052 --> 00:37:52.280
He gave us the Holy Spirit, our Comforter, our standby.

00:37:52.280 --> 00:38:01.670
He made a mansion for you with gold streets.

00:38:14.585 --> 00:38:15.805
Well, praise the Lord.

00:38:15.805 --> 00:38:17.740
Thank you for joining us today.

00:38:19.100 --> 00:38:21.747
Click that notification bell, the like button, and the subscribe button.

00:38:23.133 --> 00:38:26.463
We'll be back again tomorrow to pray more with y'all.

00:38:29.340 --> 00:38:30.740
Thank you, Brandon.

00:38:33.319 --> 00:38:37.740
Subscribe, click the notification bell.

00:38:47.319 --> 00:38:48.459
Hopefully, this blessed you.

00:38:49.599 --> 00:38:51.200
Comment something nice down below.

00:38:53.508 --> 00:38:55.251
Help us with the algorithm.

00:38:59.075 --> 00:39:00.335
God bless you all.

00:39:02.926 --> 00:39:06.180
Remember, put a smile on your face and a song in your heart.

00:39:06.180 --> 00:39:07.480
Jesus loves you so much.

00:39:13.344 --> 00:39:14.160
Bye-bye.
